elee classes (non-hybrids for the most part) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uxicantempestwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xican TempestWolf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/13/02 8:46:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27125.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Weeeeee.</span><hr size=1> We did it to spite you.<br><br>Did it work? <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=63622">Xican's profile</a><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=108458">Ashen's Profile</a><BR><i>It's better to swallow blood than pride.</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umissfoxfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Miss Foxfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/13/02 9:53:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27125.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gwynhyfar.homestead.com/files/hm9.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weeeeee.</span><hr size=1> <i>I am wondering why druids are fussing so much about being unbalanced, or a broken class.</i><br><br>You haven't been doing much thorough reading. Nobody said we were imbalanced 1-50 gameplay-wise or 1-60 exp-group-wise. You should read the State of the Druid again if you think we are talking about anything but raid issues.<br><br><br><i>im mostly just curious about why druids think they are more deserving of verants attention, or in more need of balancing than other classes that are unquestionabley broken.</i><br><br>You really have missed the point. Nobody said the druid class was "more deserving" of VI's attention. Let me put this in simple terms: Melee balancing was finished; the melee classes got their treatment. Now caster balancing is the issue, so we're bringing up our concerns in LIGHT of this project. We aren't here to specifically address the needs of other casters, but you can be assured that most of us realize that mages and necros need work as well and that we're not the only class that "deserves" VI's attention.<br><br><br><i>druids are a strong class, jack of all trades; ok at heals , ok at direct damage, ok at dots, ok at buffs - just thank god you arent "twitch bitch" or a "mod rod whore" and that is your only purpose on raids.</i><br><br>If only it were that simple. The "jack of all trades" role is one we practice on raids as well, but we are best suited as -- guess what? -- secondary healers because we are a priest class with a large enough mana pool to dedicate to the task. Shamans have more to do on raids (I know they don't stack well, that's a separate issue). Besides, Torpor is a heal you'd never want to throw on your main tank without some big consequences. However, paladins definitely have the advantage now since encounters involve AEs. Can you see that this isn't about being jack of all trades?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uawhisltle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AWhisltle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/13/02 9:57:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27125.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weeeeee.</span><hr size=1> at least u get to