wrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ustormhaven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormhaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FAQ/Index Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/14/02 2:22:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27125.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web2.airmail.net/naomi/amalgam/forum/stormhaven.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weeeeee.</span><hr size=1> Awhistle, I'm taking your post with a grain of salt.  Assuming that you actually want a discussion with this.  I think your approach might have been a little caustic, therefore the replies your post has generated are as acidic as your own.<br><br>First off,if you read the petition generated by the Druid's Grove there is no mention to whether we think other classes are in need of repair, or if our need is greater than the other classes.  Now, how did we grab people's attention?  Someone told someone who told someone else.  Honestly, the day after Caster's Realm posted the petition on their frontpage is when the petition got the most attention.  It's not hard to get on many EQ site's frontpages if you are truly recognized as &quot;speaking on behalf of a class.&quot;  In other words, if a Rogue or Monk petition started on the Safehouse/Monkly Business, the moderators of those boards would probably generate a fair amount of fuss relatively easily.  Now, assume Monkly Buis. wasn't around - instead there were 40 different boards and no unified voice to speak for monks as a whole.  Well those people probably wouldn't get as much attention.<br><br>The petition brought up by the Druid's Grove is one reaching out to the druid community.  Once the community came to a relative agreement on what needs to be done, the moderators of this forum started advertising the petition.  Have no doubt - people from Verant do monitor message boards and EQ websites.  They may have their hands tied when it comes to posting their personal opinion, but they can mention it to people who can speak for the company and address concerns.<br><br>Druids have no set role in raids - secondary healers is not a role, it's a part we fill.  <br><br>I'm not sure what server you play on, Awhistle, but high level mages (58+) are pretty few and far between on my server.  So when one is freelancing, they're usually pretty welcome on raids.  The 3x mod rods, focus items, and COH is usually enough to net them a spot.  Not to mention the fact that their epic pets are pretty incredible.<br><br>Necros suffer a fade comparable to the druid - there's too many of them.  So it's not that there's no need for a necro on a raid, it's that there's already three there.  <br><br>However, a necro's got some pretty scary stats if you know how to play them correctly.  Ideally the necros are used to &quot;twitch&quot; the clerics during long fights.  However I know a few necros that argue that they're more beneficial as damage dealers.  With their lich form and Funeral Pyre DoT, they do massive amounts of damage.  In a pinch, they can also use Mind Wrack to recover/drain mana.  Get a few necros in a group and this is a pretty evil little spell.  The fact that a well played necro never needs a heal is something to consider too.<br><br>Therefore, you might want to think a little more before you speak.  The same arguments that you're using against druids can be turned rather easily to an argument against necros.  In the end, druids aren't saying that we need to be fixed before anyone else, we're saying that we are broken in the end game, and the old cliche` that we were overpowered pre-50's is no longer a good enough excuse to not address the problems of our class.  It is not the duty of the Druid's Grove to hatch petitions for all the other classes of EQ - if you feel that the necro class needs to be revamped, I suggest that you start looking at how you can organize a similar effort.<br> <p><body link="#FFFFFF" vlink="#CCCCCC"><table border="0" bgcolor="#002675" cellpadding="4">  <tr>    <td width="100" bgcolor="#000000"><font face="Arial"><img src="http://web2.airmail.net/naomi/cards/storm1x2.jpg" width="100" height="200"></font></td>    <td width="250"><font color="#FFFFFF"><font size="4" face="Arial Black"><a href="http://www.elementofdarkness.com/eqi/inv.asp?char=197">Stormhaven the Druid</a></font>      <font face="Arial">    <br><font size="2">=============================</font>    <br><font size="2">Cazic Thule Server    <br>Wood Elf Hierophant of the 60th Level</font><br>    <br><font size="2"><a href="http://web2.airmail.net/naomi">Webmaster</a></font><a href="http://web2.airmail.net/naomi"><font size="2">      of SunWolf Designs</font></a></font></font></td>  </tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubuzweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>buzweaver</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/14/02 7:52:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27125.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.100megsfree.com/ktcrhp/druid.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weeeeee.</span><hr size=1> Hail all,<br><br>In the Manifesto there are more references to Healing, the inability to heal, the desire to heal better, to AOE heal, than anything else.  Healing is the least of my concerns nor should it be the factor that makes us group desirable. <br><br>This healing element of the Manifesto is what I disagreed with the most. Druids heal just fine. I would gladly set