EF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=46008">Cobbyl Treehuggyr</A></BR>Preserver of <A HREF="http://www.reviction.lohnetwork.com">Reviction</a></BR>Librarian of <A HREF="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove">The Druid's Grove</A></BR><i>All that is gold does not glitter/ Not all those who wander are lost/ The old that is strong does not wither/ Deep roots are not reached by the frost.</i></BR></center></HTML></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FAQ/Index Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/14/02 9:53:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27125.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: why</span><hr size=1> <b>The SotD is directed at a druid's role in a raid-type situation. </b><br><br><br>Correct.  And thus the proposed changes aimed at healing, buffing, and inflicting damage.  Some also are aimed at giving <i>more</i> druids a role on a high level raid.<br><br>All of the healing changes are primarily aimed at high level raiding, although they do have spillover benefits for other group situations.  <br><br>Of our two main forms of inflicting damage, our DDs seem to be fairly good in comparison to the wizards, while our DoT line stopped short, hence the DoT proposal.   Given our inability to reduce aggro, the DoT has an advantage in spreading out the damage over a short period of time (and since many mobs on high level raids take several minutes to kill, repeatd applications of DoTs add up).  With Fire and Cold covered by our top DDs, Magic-based damage would be covered by our DoT.  The main downside is stackability.<br><br>Of course these changes do have spillover effects for non-raid situations, but then, so do all the raid-level abilities of other classes.  Of all the proposed changes, the Group Heal is the one most directly aimed at high level raiding.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utidaljade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tidaljade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Social Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/14/02 10:05:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27125.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.truepath.com/jadae/Jade_copy.JPG width=102 height=116></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: why</span><hr size=1> lol what a gem :p <p><center><table border=0><tr><td> Uberbunnz of <a href="http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg">The Tribunal Server</a></td><td><img src="http://members.truepath.com/jadae/bunclover.jpg"></td><td>Social Mod of <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove">The Druid's Grove</a></td></tr></table></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulinwen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Linwen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/14/02 11:59:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27125.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: why</span><hr size=1> First off...<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Slap my ass and call me Tunare!<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->That's too dang funny.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> a price you pay for picking the druid class is not being excellent at any one thing, even if that means (god forbid) your only a secondary healer on raids.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Actually, we can only be considered &quot;secondary&quot; healers in a raid if you only categorize healers as primary/secondary.  As it stands now, druids are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> at best</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> third rate healers (and I could argue that we are fifth best).  As mobs do more damage, tanks have more hitpoints, mobs AE more, all secondary healers need more healing power to keep up.<br><br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> you have to realize that as a druid lvl 1-60 you can basically do anything you want: DoT, DD, Heal, Buff, (not to mention port).<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Geez, how did I ever manage to die?<br><br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Clerics heal, warriors tank, wizards nuke - they can basically only do this 1-60.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Actually, this statement is a pretty convenient gross oversimplication of encounters in Everquest.  Clerics also buff and wizards can also port - both of which you penalize druids for.<br><br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> you were best soloer 1-60,<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Do you really play a necromancer?  You firmly believe that a druid from 1 through 60 is a better at soloing than a necromancer?  Or a monk?  Or a shaman?  Or a mage?  Druids are good at soloing, yes.  Necromancers own that territory most of the time, in my opinion.  Mages/monks/shaman are better around the post-50 levels.<br><br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> and now you want uber heal power<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Not really, just better healing power.  As I mentioned earlier, it's to compensate for the increase in DPS and player hitpoints.  You cannot continue in this game to increase both the damage dealt and the level of player hitpoints without also increasing the healing power of the healers.  That doesn't apply to just druids.<br><br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> live with it<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->We are.  Part of living with it involves trying to get some changes made to our class to deal with changes in the game.  Deal with it.<br><br>*****<br><br>Do I want better increases in my direct damage, damage over time and mana regeneration or whatever?  Heck, if Verant in their wisdom decides I should have those abilities, I'll use them.  But I'm not asking for them.  Personally, I'd be happy just to see an upgrade to our healing abilities.  I feel some form of group heal would really help.  Oh, and lose the silly snare effect on the epic, mmkay?  Thanks.<br><br>Keep in mind too, druids asking for a group heal aren't doing so to save <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> our</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> butts.  As a secondary healer, we are asking for that to save <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> your</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> butt.<br><br>*****<br><br>As a side note, is it just me or can you identify all trolls by their inability to capitalize or punctuate?  When did that become &quot;cool&quot;? <p><hl><br><i><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=19005>Linwen</a></i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uloeganwolfheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Loegan Wolfheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/14/02 1:35:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27125.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: why<